# Implementation Plan - Phase 1: Project Setup and Folder Structure

This plan covers the initialization and setup of the Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor project. We will set up both the backend (Node.js/Express) and frontend (React/Vite/TailwindCSS) with their basic configurations.

## Proposed Folder Structure

We will structure the project into two main directories: `backend` and `frontend` in the workspace root: [Collaborative Document Editor](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor).

### Backend Structure
- `backend/` - Contains all server-side logic, database configuration, authentication, and WebSocket handling.
  - `config/` - Database and helper configurations.
    - [db.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/config/db.js) - MongoDB database connection setup.
  - `controllers/` - Functions that handle incoming HTTP requests (auth, documents).
    - `authController.js` - User registration, login, and profile fetching logic.
    - `documentController.js` - CRUD operations for documents.
  - `middleware/` - Custom Express middleware functions.
    - `authMiddleware.js` - Validates JWT tokens to protect routes.
  - `models/` - Mongoose database schemas.
    - `User.js` - User database schema (username, email, password).
    - `Document.js` - Document database schema (title, content/Yjs-state, owner, collaborators).
  - `routes/` - Express route mappings to controllers.
    - `authRoutes.js` - Authentication API endpoints.
    - `documentRoutes.js` - Document API endpoints.
  - `sockets/` - Socket.IO event handlers.
    - `documentSocket.js` - Collab editing sync and presence/cursor handlers.
  - [.env](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/.env) - Local configuration and secret environment variables.
  - [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/server.js) - Entry point of the Express server that binds HTTP & WebSockets.
  - `package.json` - Backend project metadata and dependencies.

### Frontend Structure
- `frontend/` - Contains the React single-page application.
  - `src/` - Application source code.
    - `components/` - Reusable UI widgets.
      - `Editor.jsx` - Tiptap collab text editor wrapper.
      - `Navbar.jsx` - Navigation bar with login/logout status.
      - `CollaboratorList.jsx` - List of active users editing the document.
    - `context/` - Global React Contexts.
      - `AuthContext.jsx` - State for logged-in user and token validation.
    - `pages/` - Views corresponding to routing pathways.
      - `Login.jsx` - Login portal interface.
      - `Register.jsx` - Sign up screen interface.
      - `Dashboard.jsx` - Main view lists documents and lets users create new ones.
      - `DocumentPage.jsx` - Interactive document editing page.
    - `services/` - Modules interacting with external endpoints.
      - `api.js` - Axios instance and helper methods for API calls.
      - `socket.js` - Socket.IO client instance and connection state.
    - [main.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/main.jsx) - Mounts the React application.
    - [App.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/App.jsx) - Main router and application wrapper.
    - [index.css](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/index.css) - Global stylesheets with Tailwind CSS imports.
  - `index.html` - HTML skeleton document.
  - `vite.config.js` - Configures Vite build system and dev server rules.
  - `tailwind.config.js` - Stylesheet configuration for theme customization.
  - `package.json` - Frontend dependencies and script shortcuts.

